1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,471
Now here is where it gets spicy,  slow down for a second.

2
00:00:05,421 --> 00:00:07,763
Let this sink in.

3
00:00:07,763 --> 00:00:20,223
A follower is considered in-sync if it has fetched all messages from the leader within replica.lag.time.max.ms (default thirty thousand ms).

4
00:00:20,223 --> 00:00:29,776
If a follower falls behind (due to network slowness, GC pauses, or disk I/O), it's removed from the ISR.

5
00:00:29,776 --> 00:00:33,434
When it catches up again, it rejoins.

6
00:00:33,434 --> 00:00:40,342
This is the concept that made me go from 'maybe I'll crack it' to 'I KNOW I'll crack it.

